description:
&lt;p&gt;Following additional commissioner investment to support the development of services to people with autism , Lancashire and South Cumbria are developing an Multi-disciplinary outreach team to support young adults /adults with a diagnosis of autism and additional mental health or behavioral needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team will work closely with mental Health services to offer specialist advice to support colleagues and to prevent hospital admissions when appropriate. The team will also provide intensive support when required to people in crisis who do not meet the criteria for support from mental health services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The MDT team will be led by a Consultant Nurse and will include OT, Psychology ,Psychiatry and nurses. Although the core hours of the team will be Monday-Friday the team will need to be flexible to work over 7 days 8am -8pm when needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are an enthusiastic SLT with experience of supporting people with autism who also have additional complex needs this Band 7 post offers an exciting opportunity to develop clinical and leadership skills and shape the development of a new service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join a growing number of SLTs in Learning Disabilities, Mental Health and Forensic Services who meet regularly to offer clinical supervision and develop good practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LSCFT has an active AHP network and can be followed on @LSCFTAHPs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suzanne Barber (Professional Lead SLT) on 01282 628225 or Christine Hutchinson (Consultant Nurse) on 01772 777499&lt;/p&gt;
